If Z - Y - X = 0 Then how do we get Y + X From the original equation, Z - Y - X = 0 (Taking Y to the other side) Z - X = Y (And taking X to the other side) Z - Y = X Therefore, Y + X = (Z - X) + (Z - Y) (Taking like terms we have) 2Z - X - Y So Y + Z = 2Z - X - Y
